5 SECTION 9. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 367 IS CREATED TO
6 READ AS FOLLOWS:
7 (1) (a) A violation of Section 4, 5, 6, or 7 of this Act shall be deemed to be an
8 unfair, false, misleading, or deceptive act or practice in the conduct of trade
9 or commerce in violation of KRS 367.170.
10 (b) All of the remedies, powers, and duties provided to the Attorney General or
11 any other person under KRS 367.110 to 367.300, and the penalties provided
12 in KRS 367.990, pertaining to acts and practices declared unlawful by KRS
13 367.170, shall apply with equal force and effect to a violation of this section.
14 (2) (a) The remedies and penalties prescribed in this section shall be cumulative.
15 (b) This section shall not be construed to limit or restrict the powers, duties,
16 remedies, or penalties available to the Attorney General, the
17 Commonwealth, or any other person under any other statutory or common
18 law.
