1 Section 11. KRS 304.9-295 is amended to read as follows:
2 (1) This section shall apply to individuals who hold licenses or lines of authority
3 requiring continuing education each biennium.
4 (2) The continuing education biennial compliance date for an individual resident
5 licensee shall be as follows:
6 (a) A licensee whose birth date is in an even-numbered year shall satisfy
7 continuing education requirements on or before the last day of the licensee's
8 birth month in the even-numbered year. A licensee shall show proof of
9 compliance to the commissioner within sixty (60) days after the continuing
10 education biennial compliance date. If the licensee has not held the license for
11 one (1) year, the compliance date is adjusted to the next even-numbered year
12 and each subsequent even-numbered year thereafter. If the license becomes
13 inactive and reissued within a twelve (12) month period, the compliance date
14 shall remain the same;
15 (b) A licensee whose birth date is in an odd-numbered year shall satisfy
16 continuing education requirements and show proof of compliance to the
17 commissioner on or before the last day of the licensee's birth month in the
18 odd-numbered year. A licensee shall show proof of compliance to the
19 commissioner within sixty (60) days after the continuing education biennial
20 compliance date. If the licensee has not held the license for one (1) year, the
21 compliance date is adjusted to the next odd-numbered year and each
22 subsequent odd-numbered year thereafter. If the license becomes inactive and
23 reissued within a twelve (12) month period, the compliance date shall remain
24 the same.
25 (3) This section shall not apply to:
26 (a) Limited lines of authority under agent licenses, as exempted by the
27 commissioner in accordance with KRS 304.9-230;
Page 35 of 44
HB056820.100 - 473 - XXXX 4/2/2026 12:15 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 568/EN
1 (b) Licensees not licensed for one (1) full year prior to the end of the applicable
2 continuing education biennium;
3 (c) Licensees holding nonresident licenses who have met the continuing
4 education requirements of their home state and whose home state gives credit
5 to Kentucky resident licensees on the same basis; or
6 (d) Licensees maintaining their licenses for the sole purpose of receiving
7 renewals or deferred commissions and providing the department with a
8 supporting affidavit.
9 (4) A licensee, who holds an agent license and who is not exempt under subsection (3)
10 of this section, shall satisfactorily complete a minimum of twenty-four (24) hours of
11 continuing education courses, of which three (3) hours shall have a course
12 concentration in ethics, during each continuing education biennium.
13 (5) Beginning July 31, 2012, an individual who holds an independent or public adjuster
14 license and who is not exempt under KRS 304.9-430(10)[ or (11)], shall
15 satisfactorily complete a minimum of twenty-four (24) hours of continuing
16 education courses, of which three (3) hours shall have a course concentration in
17 ethics in accordance with subsection (4) of this section. Continuing education hours
18 shall be reported to the commissioner on a biennial basis in conjunction with the
19 licensee's renewal in accordance with subsection (10) of this section.
20 (6) Only continuing education courses approved by the commissioner shall be used to
21 satisfy the continuing education requirement of subsection (4) of this section and
22 any other continuing education requirement of this chapter.
23 (a) The continuing education courses which meet the commissioner's standards
24 for continuing education requirements are:
25 1. Any part of the Life Underwriter Training Council life course
26 curriculum;
27 2. Any part of the Health Underwriter Training Council health course
