26 Section 13. KRS 342.908 is amended to read as follows:
27 (1) The commissioner shall notify a guaranty fund if the commissioner has knowledge
Page 40 of 44
HB056820.100 - 473 - XXXX 4/2/2026 12:15 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 568/EN
1 that any member of the guaranty fund has failed to timely pay workers'
2 compensation benefits required by this chapter or if a court of competent
3 jurisdiction has declared the member to be bankrupt or insolvent.
4 (2) In the event of issuance of a certificate of default, the commissioner shall call all
5 security and transfer it to the appropriate guaranty fund created pursuant to this
6 section. The commissioner shall also immediately notify, by certified mail, the
7 guaranty fund and order the guaranty fund to assume the workers' compensation
8 obligations of the member required in this chapter. The guaranty fund shall
9 commence payment of these obligations within fourteen (14) days of receipt of
10 notification and order of the commissioner. Payment shall be made to claimants
11 whose entitlement to benefits can be ascertained by the guaranty fund with or
12 without proceedings before the Department of Workers' Claims or a court of
13 competent jurisdiction. Upon assumption of the obligations of a member by a
14 guaranty fund, the guaranty fund shall have the right to immediate possession of
15 any security, and the custodian, surety, or issuer of any irrevocable letter of credit
16 shall turn over the security, proceeds of the surety bond, or letter of credit to the
17 guaranty fund, together with the interest that has accrued since the date of the
18 member's insolvency. The guaranty fund may administer payment of benefits or it
19 may retain a third party to do so.
20 (3) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, any cash, securities, irrevocable letters
21 of credit, specific excess or aggregate excess insurance proceeds, or any other
22 security deposited or posted in accordance with this section shall be used first, when
23 due, to pay workers' compensation claims. After the security has been exhausted,
24 the payment of workers' compensation claims from member assessments may be
25 made. Where the guaranty fund member-assessment account is used to pay workers'
26 compensation claims on an emergency or an interim basis, pending receipt by the
27 guaranty fund of security which is due but not yet received, the member-assessment
