HB056820.100 - 473 - XXXX 4/2/2026 12:15 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 568/EN
1 account shall be reimbursed for payment from the security when it is received, and
2 the priorities stated above shall thereafter apply.
3 (4) (a) To the extent necessary to secure funds for the initial establishment of each
4 guaranty fund member-assessment account, the board of directors of each
5 guaranty fund created pursuant to this section shall levy assessments based on
6 the premium of each individual self-insured employer, as defined and
7 calculated pursuant to KRS 342.0011(28), for members of the Kentucky
8 individual self-insurers guaranty fund and for the Kentucky coal employers
9 self-insurance guaranty fund, and KRS 342.0011(24) for the Kentucky group
10 self-insurance guaranty fund, but no such assessments shall ever exceed, in
11 the aggregate, from all members of a single guaranty fund, an amount in
12 excess of one million dollars ($1,000,000) at any given time.
13 (b) The assessments shall be made at a maximum annual assessment of:
14 1. One-half of one percent (0.5%) of the premium for each member of the
15 Kentucky individual self-insurance guaranty fund as defined and
16 calculated pursuant to KRS 342.0011(28);
17 2. Two percent (2%) of the premium for each member of the Kentucky
18 coal employers guaranty fund as defined and calculated pursuant to KRS
19 342.0011(28); and
20 3. Three-fourths of one percent (0.75%) of the premium for each member
21 of the Kentucky group self-insurance guaranty fund as defined and
22 calculated pursuant to KRS 342.0011(24).
23 (5) The initial assessment for each guaranty fund created pursuant to this section shall
24 be for an amount equal to five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000), to be levied
25 and collected within a one (1) year period. There shall be no reassessments against
26 any member unless the current balance of such guaranty fund created pursuant this
27 section is insufficient after deducting the amount paid for or reserved for
